%text
 Each $x$ in each $(x,y)\in R$ maps to a single $y (=3)$. Hence, the given relation is a function. In fact, the given relation is a \underline\text{constant function} 
 Note that this is different from the case where a single $x$ maps to multiple $y's$. In that case the relation would not have been a function%
